article.headline: Utah State 71, Georgia Southern 61
article.story: FAIRBANKS, Alaska (AP) -- Jaycee Carroll scored 19 points to lead Utah State past Georgia Southern 71-61 Thursday night in a first-round matchup at the Top of the World Classic featuring two 20-game winners from last season. The Aggies (1-0) led by as many as 19 points in the first half in the season opener for both schools. Utah State made 60 percent of its shots in taking a 44-27 halftime lead. Georgia Southern (0-1) rallied behind guards Terry Williams (15 points) and Elton Nesbitt (14 points), who helped pull the Eagles to 63-57 with about five minutes left. But Carroll hit two free throws and followed with a pair of long field goals. The Aggies play Central Florida in Saturday's second round, and Georgia Southern faces host Alaska-Fairbanks. In other first-round play Friday, it's Portland vs. Northwestern and Western Michigan vs. New Mexico State.
